Journal includes diary entries that document Lowry's health, her father's death, her relationship with her mother, meditations on death and growing old, and her reactions to the terrorist attacks on September 11th. Also notes, to-dos, grocery lists, collages, stamps, watercolor and ink sketches. Pasted in are news clippings, photos of Lowry and husband Jon Gothold, lab results, and other ephemera.
This is one of 119 art journals, ranging from circa 1973-2007, in Lowry's papers.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
